            "content": {
                "raw": "I would consider something like this:\n\n\n```\n#!bash\n\n        echo \"Looks like you're on Midway.\"\n        echo\n        echo \" ******************************************\"\n        echo \" * It may be better to use the yt module! *\"\n        echo \" *                                        *\"\n        echo \" *   $ module load yt                     *\"\n        echo \" *                                        *\"\n        echo \" * or to load the latest development rel. *\"\n        echo \" *                                        *\"\n        echo \" *   $ module load yt/3.0                 *\"\n        echo \" *                                        *\"\n        echo \" ******************************************\"\n```\n\nBut it means hard-coding the version number of the development version.  I'd consider making stable and devel aliases, but we don't really have a policy at the RCC for that.",
                "html": "<p>I would consider something like this:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span>        <span class=\"nb\">echo</span> <span class=\"s2\">&quot;Looks like you&#39;re on Midway.&quot;</span>\n        <span class=\"nb\">echo</span>\n        <span class=\"nb\">echo</span> <span class=\"s2\">&quot; ******************************************&quot;</span>\n        <span class=\"nb\">echo</span> <span class=\"s2\">&quot; * It may be better to use the yt module! *&quot;</span>\n        <span class=\"nb\">echo</span> <span class=\"s2\">&quot; *                                        *&quot;</span>\n        <span class=\"nb\">echo</span> <span class=\"s2\">&quot; *   </span>$<span class=\"s2\"> module load yt                     *&quot;</span>\n        <span class=\"nb\">echo</span> <span class=\"s2\">&quot; *                                        *&quot;</span>\n        <span class=\"nb\">echo</span> <span class=\"s2\">&quot; * or to load the latest development rel. *&quot;</span>\n        <span class=\"nb\">echo</span> <span class=\"s2\">&quot; *                                        *&quot;</span>\n        <span class=\"nb\">echo</span> <span class=\"s2\">&quot; *   </span>$<span class=\"s2\"> module load yt/3.0                 *&quot;</span>\n        <span class=\"nb\">echo</span> <span class=\"s2\">&quot; *                                        *&quot;</span>\n        <span class=\"nb\">echo</span> <span class=\"s2\">&quot; ******************************************&quot;</span>\n</pre></div>\n\n\n<p>But it means hard-coding the version number of the development version.  I'd consider making stable and devel aliases, but we don't really have a policy at the RCC for that.</p>",
                "markup": "markdown"
            },
